          "text": "On St. Helena, Napoleon rose before dawn and walked the cliff path alone, his greatcoat tight against the wind. He traced battles in the sand with a stick \u2014 Austerlitz, Marengo \u2014 names that still clattered like distant guns. A gull wheeled and scattered his thoughts; he smiled at the absurdity of maps that once bent to his will. At noon he sat beneath a thorn tree and opened a small notebook, writing of tides and chess moves, of regrets softened by time. When evening fell, he folded his notes and watched the sun fall into the ocean, as if the world itself were closing a chapter."
